HEADWORD: Blindfish
<hw>Blind"fish`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A small fish
(<spn>Amblyopsis spel⟦ae⟧us</spn>) destitute of eyes, found in the
waters of the Mammoth Cave, in Kentucky. Related fishes from other caves
take the same name.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

